Look at that. `Blynk.virtualWrite(V1, moisturePercent)`. One line. That's it. Blynk handles the HTTP request, the connection, the authentication — everything. You just tell it which virtual pin to write to and what value to send.

That's the trade-off. ThingSpeak teaches you how HTTP actually works. Blynk abstracts it away and gives you shiny widgets. One makes you smarter. The other makes you faster. Choose your fighter.

